mat Problem\" has been identified - tokens like \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00) are metaprogramming artifacts, not actual causal research tokens. The proposed hybrid formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` should distinguish these from true research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) on 200 pulses to test if the formula separates \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5). Compare against binary thresholds documented in CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Type:** Strategy C - Hybrid Scoring\r\n**Goal:** Test if score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nThe hybrid formula will:\r\n1. **Dampen constant-format tokens**: score(\"for next instantiation\") = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 (still high!)\r\n2. **Preserve research tokens**: score(\"Phase 1\") = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 (unchanged)\r\n3. **Reward mid-frequency causal tokens**: score(\"temporal attention\") = 0.7 × min(1, 40/120) = 0.7 × 0.33 = 0.23\r\n\r\n**Problem detected:** The formula still doesn't penalize freq=160 tokens enough!\r\n\r\n### Revised Formula\r\nTo truly separate constant-format from research:\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × freq_penalty(T)\r\nwhere freq_penalty(T) = \r\n  - 0.0 if freq(T) > 140 (constant - suppress completely)\r\n  - freq(T)/120 if 3 ≤ freq(T) ≤ 120 (normal range)\r\n  - 1.0 if freq(T) < 3 (rare - uncertain)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Test Plan\r\n1. Extract all tokens from 200 pulses\r\n2. Compute: CFI(T), freq(T), hybrid_score(T)\r\n3. Compare token distributions across three categories:\r\n   - **Constant-format** (expected: freq>140, CFI>0.95)\r\n   - **Research trajectory** (expected: 3≤freq≤120, CFI>0.5)\r\n   - **Noise** (expected: freq<3 OR freq>140 AND CFI<0.5)\r\n4. Evaluate precision/recall vs ground truth from Strategy A/B\r\n\r\n## Results (In Progress)\r\n*To be filled after running on pulse corpus*\r\nfile: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:41:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381366042}}
