{"type":"message","id":"daeea3b9","parentId":"7b763cab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:42:53.766Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bi3yisj9jyse_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 154221\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n2. A key experiment was run: CFI Compression Experiment with findings about:\r\n   - CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 being too aggressive\r\n   - Constant format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.00) being metaprogramming artifacts\r\n   - Need for three-dimensional filter\r\n   - Proposed hybrid scoring: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\n3. Pending action: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to run the hybrid scoring experiment to test if the formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes constant format tokens from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create an experiment document for the hybrid scoring test\r\n2. Define the methodology clearly\r\n3. Set up the comparison against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nLet me write a focused, concrete action to advance this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0) are metaprogramming artifacts with zero information, while \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) represents true research trajectory. A hybrid scoring formula has been proposed but not yet tested.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment specification with the proposed formula and methodology to test whether score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) can distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens on a 200-pulse dataset.\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Status:** DESIGNED, pending execution  \r\n**Related:** `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nThe binary threshold approach (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60) fails because it treats CFI and frequency as independent constraints. A multiplicative scoring function will better capture their joint distribution:\r\n\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Predictions:**\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | Binary Score | Hybrid Score | Verdict |\r\n|------------|------|-----|--------------|--------------|---------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | FAIL (freq≥60) | 1.00 (too high!) | Problem |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | FAIL | 1.00 | Problem |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | FAIL | 0.96 | Problem |\r\n| Research token (e.g., \"TemporalAttention\") | 45 | 0.72 | PASS | 0.72 | Correct |\r\n| Rare signal (freq=3, CFI=0.9) | 3 | 0.90 | PASS | 0.225 | Correct |\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\n- 200 pulses from `data/pulses/` (80/20 train/test split)\r\n- Train on first 160 pulses, test on last 40\r\n- Evaluate precision/recall on held-out test set\r\n\r\n### Token Scoring Comparison\r\n\r\n**Strategy A (Binary - baseline):**  \r\nfilter(T) = (CFI(T) ≥ 0.7) AND (freq(T) < 60)\r\n\r\n**Strategy B (Binary - CFI only):**  \r\nfilter(T) = (CFI(T) ≥ 0.5)\r\n\r\n**Strategy C (Hybrid scoring - proposed):**  \r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)  \r\nfilter(T) = score(T) ≥ 0.35\r\n\r\n### Ground Truth Definition\r\nTokens are \"meaningful\" if they appear in ≥3 pulses AND are NOT in the constant-format exclusion list:\r\n- Tokens appearing in >95% of pulses\r\n- Tokens matching regex: `^(pulse_|Phase \\d+|completed at:)`\r\n- Tokens that are purely metaprogramming: \"for next instantiation\", \"stateless\", \"discontinuous\"\r\n\r\n### Evaluation Metrics\r\n- **Precision:** % of filtered tokens that are ground-truth meaningful\r\n- **Recall:** % of ground-truth meaningful tokens that pass filter\r\n- **F1:** Harmonic mean of precision and recall\r\n- **Constant-filter rate:** % of constant-format tokens correctly rejected\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcomes\r\n\r\n1. Strategy A (binary) = 56.5% precision, ~7% recall (from CFI Compression Synthesis)\r\n2. Strategy B (CFI-only) = TBD but likely high recall, low precision\r\n3. Strategy C (hybrid) = Should achieve balanced precision/recall by down-weighting high-freq tokens\r\n\r\n## Key Test\r\nCan Strategy C filter out \"for next instantiation\" (score=1.00) while keeping \"Phase 1\" (score=0.96)?\r\n\r\n**Problem identified:** Both score ~1.0. The formula doesn't solve the constant-format problem.\r\n\r\n## Revised Formula (if needed)\r\n\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) × penalty(T)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere `penalty(T)` = 0.1 if T matches constant-format pattern, else 1.0\r\n\r\nThis would give:\r\n- \"for next instantiation\": 1.0 × 0.1 = 0.1 (filtered out)\r\n- \"Phase 1\": 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96 (kept)\r\n- Research token (freq=45): 0.72 × 0.375 = 0.27 (\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:42:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381373763}}
{"type":"message","id":"08ef7308","parentId":"daeea3b9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:43:06.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the complete picture from the latest pulse log. Let me provide a concise summary.","thinkingSignature":"8f7b8891e9ae0c49158aa19e847742290db60c204e5a8b588d1a7603a58b07ed"},{"type":"text","text":"## Pulse Cycle Summary — 2026-03-24 15:42 UTC\n\n**Status:** Active research — CFI compression project (Phases 0 & 1 complete, experiments ongoing)\n\n**Key findings from this pulse:**\n- The hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` was designed and logged to `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md`\n- **Critical problem identified:** The formula still fails to separate constant-format tokens from research tokens — both \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.0) and \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) score ~1.0\n- **Revised formula proposed:** Add a `penalty(T) = 0.1` multiplier for tokens matching constant-format patterns, which would push metaprogramming artifacts down to ~0.1 while keeping real research tokens at ~0.96\n\n**Pending work:**\n- Execute the hybrid experiment on 200-pulse dataset (80/20 train/test split)\n- Evaluate precision/recall for Strategies A, B, and C against ground truth\n- Finalize Phase 1 synthesis with validated formula\n\n**Proposed mutations waiting:** 0 (design complete, awaiting execution next cycle)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4309,"output":293,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774381373768}}
